                        "name": "cgmartin",
                        "displayName": "Chris Martin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Saw a technique on the mailinglist (by graham.anderson) that is much more elegant.\n\n{code}\nclass My_Controller_PreDispatchPlugin extends Zend_Controller_Plugin_Abstract\n{\n    public function preDispatch(Zend_Controller_Request_Abstract $request)\n    {\n        $front      = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance();\n        $dispatcher = $front->getDispatcher();\n\n        $test       = new Zend_Controller_Request_Http();\n        $test->setParams(array(\n                    'action'     => $request->getActionName(),\n                    'controller' => $request->getControllerName(),\n                    'module'     => $request->getModuleName()\n              )    \n        );\n\n        if ($dispatcher->isDispatchable($test)) {\n            \/\/ ...We have a valid route\n        }\n    }\n}\n{code}",
